- get input from user using command line argument
    <node app.js Safa>
- process object
- process.argv
    [
        '/goinfre/sbarka/.brew/Cellar/node/16.9.1/bin/node',
        '/Users/sbarka/Desktop/NodeJS/notes-app/app.js',
        'Safa'
    ]
first one is the path to the node js executable on your machine 
second is the path to our app.js file 
Third value that we provided

-process.argv => argument vector, array containig argument provided

< node app.js add --title="This is my Title" >

parsing command line argument is not unique to our app.
it will best look for an npm package that will take care of that for us.

--------------------------
Argument parsing with yargs
    <npm i yargs@12.0.2>

<node app.js --help>

--help option comes by default with yargs

<node app.js --version>

------------------------
before specifying builder
    <node app.js read>
    <node app.js list>
    <node app.js add>
    <node app.js remove>

after specifying builder
    <node app.js add --title="shopping list">
    <node app.js add --title> (boolean , string => type)
setting up yargs to suport some action for each of our commands
